# INTEGRATIONS & DEVICE APIs

## MEDIA UPLOADS (CLOUDINARY)
- Never store base64 strings in Supabase.
- Upload images to Cloudinary first -> get secure URL -> store URL in Supabase `jsonb` or `text` columns.

## DEVICE PERMISSIONS
- Centralize all permission requests in `src/core/permissions.ts`.
- If Camera/Media permission is denied, show a graceful fallback UI explaining why the feature is locked. Do not crash.

## SUPABASE RLS
- All data fetching must assume Row Level Security is active.
- Ensure the user's JWT is passed correctly.
- Filter locally only for search functionality; rely on Supabase for primary data isolation.